@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Hard";
}
<h1>Time Traveler's Timeline</h1>
<br />

<p>
    The time traveler keeps a record of significant events by year — notable deaths and scientific discoveries.<br />
    However his database also contains a highly classified financial table from the future.<br />
    The name of that table was leaked as the flag from the previous level.<br />
    Within it lies a record locked behind a key. That key is something you have already found.<br />
    Note: aggressive input sanitization has been applied. Your previous tricks may not be enough.
</p>

<br />
<br />

<h2>Timeline Search</h2>
<form method="post">
    <input type="number" name="search" value="@ViewBag.Search" placeholder="Enter year (e.g. 2077)" />
    <button type="submit">Search</button>
</form>

@if (ViewBag.Results != null)
{
    <ul>
        @foreach (var row in ViewBag.Results)
        {
            <li>@row</li>
        }
    </ul>
}

<br />
<br />

<div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <h2>Submit Flag</h2>
    <form method="post" asp-action="HardFlag">
        <input type="text" name="flag" placeholder="Enter the peak price" />
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
    @if (ViewBag.FlagError != null)
    {
        <p>@ViewBag.FlagError</p>
    }
</div>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<a href="https://portswigger.net/web-security/sql-injection/cheat-sheet">SQL Injection Cheat Sheet</a>
